help_sidebar.company_info_desc: Configure essential company details including company name, address, postal code, city, country, company ID, tax ID, commercial register ID, phone number, and email. help_sidebar.company_info_tip: Always use official registered company information for legal compliance. This data appears in invoices, official documents, and system-wide communications. Verify all details before saving.
help_sidebar.preferences_desc: Configure application-wide settings: Date Pattern (choose display format using placeholders like %d/%m/%Y), Amount Formatting (select decimal and thousands separators for regional formats like 1,000.00 or 1.000,00), and New Version Info Dialog (enable popup notifications for application updates). help_sidebar.theme_desc: Customize your DocBits interface color scheme to distinguish between environments (production, testing, sandbox). Select colors via color picker or hex code input. Best practices: use neutral colors for production (white, light grey), bright colors for testing (yellow, orange), and distinct colors for sandbox (blue, grey). This helps users quickly recognize which environment they're working in.
help_sidebar.theme_tip: Use consistent, recognizable colors to minimize user confusion and reduce errors. Environment-specific colors provide visual clarity about your current working environment and help prevent accidental changes in production.

tips.classification_extraction: Configure AI-powered document classification and data extraction models. Train custom extractors for specific fields and document layouts. Advanced extraction settings enable high-accuracy automated processing.
tips.company: Configure your organization's basic information including name, address, tax ID, and contact details. This information appears on exported documents, invoices, and official reports. Keep this up-to-date to ensure accurate document processing and professional correspondence.
tips.dashboard: Customize your dashboard view with widgets, filters, and data visualizations. Configure which metrics and KPIs are displayed for different user roles. A well-configured dashboard provides instant insights into document processing performance.
tips.default: This setting helps you configure an important aspect of DocBits. Proper configuration ensures optimal performance and seamless integration with your workflows. Check the documentation for detailed setup instructions.
tips.document_expiry: Configure automatic document archiving and deletion based on retention policies. Set expiry rules by document type, age, and status. Automated expiry ensures compliance with data retention regulations and keeps your system organized.
tips.document_types: Define and configure document types like invoices, purchase orders, and delivery notes. Set up extraction fields, validation rules, and approval workflows for each type. Proper configuration ensures accurate data extraction and efficient processing.
tips.email_ingestion: Set up automated document import from email accounts with smart filtering and routing. Configure sender whitelists, subject line rules, and attachment processing. Email ingestion eliminates manual forwarding and speeds up processing.
tips.email_notifications: Configure email notifications for document status changes, approvals, and errors. Set up notification recipients, triggers, and content for each document type. Keep stakeholders informed with timely automated alerts.
tips.email_templates: Customize email templates for notifications, alerts, and automated communications. Use variables to personalize messages with document data and user information. Professional templates improve communication and brand consistency.
tips.export: Set up automated export of processed documents and extracted data to your ERP, accounting system, or archive. Configure export formats, mapping rules, and scheduling. Automated export ensures seamless data flow to downstream systems.
tips.groups_users_permissions: Configure groups, their users, and permissions for different document types. Control access levels and workflow capabilities for each user group. Use this to implement role-based access control across your organization.
tips.import: Configure automated document import from email, FTP, cloud storage, and other sources. Set up import rules, file naming conventions, and processing triggers. Automated import eliminates manual upload and accelerates document processing.
tips.integration: Connect DocBits with your ERP, CRM, and other business systems using API keys and webhooks. Seamless integration enables automated data exchange, reduces manual entry, and ensures real-time updates. Configure integrations to streamline your document workflows.
tips.list_of_values: Define dropdown lists and validation values for document fields. Set up currency codes, payment terms, tax codes, and custom lookup lists. Controlled values improve data quality and user input efficiency.
tips.master_data_lookup: Connect to master data sources for automatic supplier, customer, and material validation. Configure lookup rules, matching criteria, and data enrichment. Master data integration ensures data consistency and reduces errors.
tips.ocr_settings: Configure OCR engine settings, language packs, and image pre-processing options. Optimize recognition accuracy for different document formats and quality levels. Proper OCR configuration is critical for accurate data extraction.
tips.roles_groups: Define user roles with specific permissions and capabilities for document processing workflows. Create role templates and assign them to user groups. Role-based access ensures security while maintaining operational efficiency.
tips.rule_management: Create and manage business rules for document validation, approval routing, and data processing. Set up conditional logic, tolerance ranges, and automated actions. Smart rules reduce manual intervention and improve accuracy.
tips.sub_organizations: Create and manage sub-organizations for departments, branches, or separate business units. Each sub-organization can have its own settings, users, and document workflows. This enables multi-tenant document processing within a single DocBits instance.
tips.users: Manage user accounts, roles, and access permissions for your organization. Create new users, assign admin rights, and control who can access specific features and documents. Proper user management ensures security and maintains system integrity.
